            <figcaption>
              <p>This three course meal was made by the party under Senshi's guidance to help Laios determine who in the
                group were actually shapeshifters pretending to be his companions. For the pilaf, prepared by the
                Senshis, bite-sized meat and vegetables are cooked with rice over low heat. For the piccata, made by the
                Chilchucks, cockatrice meat is cut up then eggs and seasoning are beaten together. For the dessert, as
                made by the Marcilles, dryad fruit is peeled then boiled and mashed with spices.</p>
            </figcaption>
          </figure>

              <p>This meal is prepared by Senshi using different parts of the Red Dragon they had slain. A dough is made
                and covered with onions and cheese and baked on a lightly floured dragon scale in the dragon's
                accidentally lit insides. The tip of the dragon's tail is skinned and the meat added to a soup. Meat
                from the inside of the dragon's body is browned on the heated scales and seasoned to taste.</p>
